Upstream credit, not upstream canon
-----------------------------------
`epoko77-ai/im-not-ai` is the **origin** of this work and is credited as such.
It is not the canonical source for this plugin. It lives under a different
GitHub account, and this marketplace runs a personal capture → promotion loop
that cannot gate on write access to someone else's repository. Nothing from this
plugin has been or will be pushed upstream as part of packaging it here.

If the upstream project wants any of the v2.0 material below, it is MIT and
freely available — but that would be a deliberate contribution, not an
automatic sync.

Modifications relative to upstream v1.5
---------------------------------------
Substantial. This plugin is **v2.0.0** and is not byte-compatible with upstream.

1. **Taxonomy raised v1.5 → v2.0.** Added the Korean translation-studies lineage
   (8 번역투 types) and the post-editese literature. New patterns: `A-16`
   (영어 대명사 직역), `A-18` (관계절 좌향 수식), `A-19` (이중 조사 결합), `E-7`
   (청자 경어법 일관성). Reinforced: `A-15`, `A-7`, `F-4`, `E-2`. `A-17` is
   held pending evidence. Earlier v1.6 additions (`C-11`, `C-12`, `E-5`, `E-6`,
   `G-3`) are also included.
2. **Added a quantitative metric layer** absent upstream: `metrics.py` +
   `baseline.json` (8 metrics) and `metrics_v2.py` + `baseline_v2.json`
   (14 post-editese / T1–T8 metrics), plus a regression harness in `tests/`.
3. **Added `scholarship.md`**, the academic citation record backing the v2.0
   patterns.
4. **Fixed a path-anchoring defect** that had agents reading reference files at
   bare relative paths, which resolve against the user's working directory
   rather than the skill directory — so the rulebooks were silently never read.
5. **Instruction prose converted to English**, rewritten from the v2.0 content
   rather than translated from the older English lineage. All Korean pattern
   names, example sentences, lexicon data, scholar citations, trigger phrases,
   and user-facing output templates are preserved verbatim in Korean — that
   material is the substance of the skill, not prose.
6. **Six agent definitions dropped** as build-time scaffolding or out-of-scope;
   six ship. See README.

Academic sources
----------------
`references/scholarship.md` cites published translation-studies scholarship —
Korean (이근희, 김정우, 김도훈, 김순영, 김혜영, 이영옥, 곽은주, 조의연, 전영철,
진실로, 박옥수) and international (Baker 1993, Toury 1995, Laviosa 2002,
Chesterman 2004, Frawley 1984, Toral 2019, Sarti et al. 2022, Cho et al. 2019,
Hayase et al. 2024). Those citations are attributions to their authors' work.
No third-party text is redistributed here beyond ordinary scholarly citation.

The `baseline.json` figures derive from the KatFish (Park et al.) and LREAD
studies as cited in that file. `baseline_v2.json` cells are **estimates**, every
one flagged `_placeholder: true`; they have not been calibrated against a
non-translated Korean reference corpus. Treat v2 z-scores as directional.
